01:26:09,400 --> 01:26:13,757
I don't want a picture, I want Alex!
- But he scored very good with Lilli.

716
01:26:13,880 --> 01:26:18,351
That alone is worth the money.
You like it too, don't you?

717
01:26:18,480 --> 01:26:22,439
No wonder!
- I mean, I should try that:

718
01:26:22,920 --> 01:26:27,596
"Oh, you wanted a red wall?
Well, I've just painted it yellow.

719
01:26:28,000 --> 01:26:32,471
Yellow is also quite beautiful.
Red didn't feel right, you know. "

720
01:26:32,600 --> 01:26:37,993
20,000 Euro! I'd be fired immediately.
- He's an artist, not a decorator, Wanda.

721
01:26:38,320 --> 01:26:41,278
Awesome, an artist.
- I like it.

722
01:26:41,400 --> 01:26:45,279
Now you like it. First a huge rebellion,
that you shall go there.

723
01:26:45,400 --> 01:26:49,996
And since I don't like it, you like it!
- What do you mean now again?

724
01:26:50,120 --> 01:26:53,795
If you don't like it, I'll take it with me.
- With you? Where to?

725
01:26:53,920 --> 01:26:56,878
Well, I'll hang it up
in my room.

726
01:27:05,920 --> 01:27:06,875
Hello.

727
01:27:09,200 --> 01:27:11,760
Sara!
- Hello, Lilli!

728
01:27:13,840 --> 01:27:15,831
Hello, little Indian.

729
01:27:16,800 --> 01:27:19,360
Uncle Thomas!

730
01:27:26,120 --> 01:27:27,394
Well, you're fine?

731
01:27:35,040 --> 01:27:38,237
Next week it's a year, huh?
- Ow!

732
01:27:38,360 --> 01:27:42,319
Have you cut yourself? Badly?
- No, it's nothing.

733
01:27:43,480 --> 01:27:44,435
Thank you.

734
01:27:52,360 --> 01:27:55,193
And how does that feel?

735
01:27:58,880 --> 01:28:01,713
It'll be ok, I think.

736
01:28:03,920 --> 01:28:06,753
And the two over there?

737
01:28:09,160 --> 01:28:12,994
Do you think,
they'd grieve like that for me too?

738
01:28:17,600 --> 01:28:18,555
Lilli!

739
01:28:20,520 --> 01:28:25,389
Can this idiot stay with you?
He doesn't let me paint my picture.

740
01:28:25,520 --> 01:28:30,833
Come here, sweetheart. You'll
stay a bit with us, will you?

741
01:28:30,960 --> 01:28:33,918
Lilli, come here,
I want to show you something!

742
01:28:38,280 --> 01:28:41,909
Look, I've painted that for you.
- Thank you.

743
01:28:42,040 --> 01:28:46,830
That's us eating today. That's Grandpa
and Alex. They are waving at us.

744
01:28:46,960 --> 01:28:53,115
Let me in. Let me in.
Mom said I may play with you.

745
01:28:55,000 --> 01:28:59,915
I'm going to cut you into pieces with
my magic sword. And fry you.

746
01:29:00,040 --> 01:29:05,194
Or put you on the stove. Or I can
also cut your ears off.

747
01:29:15,600 --> 01:29:18,558
Now look what you did.

748
01:29:22,320 --> 01:29:24,880
Are you crying now?

749
01:29:35,480 --> 01:29:41,112
I want my brother back.
- You can take me as a brother.

750
01:30:24,680 --> 01:30:28,468
I think we haven't changed anything
here since Sarah's birth.

751
01:30:28,600 --> 01:30:32,559
The sofa, for example,
is really ready to be thrown out.

752
01:30:33,320 --> 01:30:37,279
Maybe you can have it upholstered.
With the baby everything starts all over again.

753
01:30:37,400 --> 01:30:41,154
I don't know why you need to change
something. It's all good.

754
01:30:41,280 --> 01:30:45,159
I will spend most the coming months
on the couch again.

755
01:30:48,480 --> 01:30:52,792
Enjoy it.
I can get the fabric.

756
01:30:52,920 --> 01:30:56,469
What would you like?
- No idea.

757
01:30:58,360 --> 01:31:04,276
Paul, why aren't you going upstairs?
Both of you!

758
01:31:05,080 --> 01:31:08,038
But you call, when it's icecream.
- No.

759
01:31:08,440 --> 01:31:11,273
Dad, you'll call us!
- Yes, sure.

760
01:31:13,640 --> 01:31:17,519
Let the filling be.
- No, it tastes good.

761
01:31:17,640 --> 01:31:21,599
A warm yellow maybe.
That's not very non-sensitive.

762
01:31:21,720 --> 01:31:25,679
True, yellow would be very nice.
- I thought you were leaving?

763
01:31:25,800 --> 01:31:28,758
So what?
- Lilli, how's it going with "Alice"?

764
01:31:29,600 --> 01:31:34,151
I imagine it's exhausting
to dance such a leading part.

765
01:31:36,080 --> 01:31:40,039
I don't play the lead anymore.
I'm fired.

766
01:31:40,720 --> 01:31:43,553
Really?
- I knew it.

767
01:31:45,600 --> 01:31:49,479
I'll call her and undo it.
You have a depression.

768
01:31:49,600 --> 01:31:53,388
No, you don't do it.
I don't want to dance "Alice" anymore.

769
01:31:53,520 --> 01:31:57,479
Musical is nothing for me.
- Wow, two years for nothing.

770
01:31:57,600 --> 01:32:01,479
You don't mean that?
- She'll dance her first leading role...

771
01:32:01,600 --> 01:32:05,479
just next year. You are behaving...
- Mind your own business.

772
01:32:05,600 --> 01:32:09,479
I don't want to dance anymore.
I just want to sing, I like it.

773
01:32:09,600 --> 01:32:13,479
What do you think how many girls
have a very nice voice?

774
01:32:13,600 --> 01:32:17,479
Are you doing this education only
to sing commercial jingles afterwards?

775
01:32:17,600 --> 01:32:21,639
Ask me why, Dad.
- Do you think I don't know it?

776
01:32:21,760 --> 01:32:26,959
Stop whining, Lilli. Do you want
Alex's death to ruin your life too?

777
01:32:27,080 --> 01:32:32,712
Sometimes I feel
I've not only lost my brother.

778
01:32:42,200 --> 01:32:45,158
Your father's right, and you know it.

779
01:32:45,840 --> 01:32:50,391
Exactly, you are in agreement.
Even if you otherwise don't agree.

780
01:32:50,520 --> 01:32:55,071
But here you are once again
a hard-hitting concrete wall.

781
01:32:56,760 --> 01:32:57,715
Awesome.

782
01:33:11,840 --> 01:33:12,795
Max?

783
01:33:16,680 --> 01:33:20,639
Ah, Lilli, again?
- What are you doing here?

784
01:33:21,360 --> 01:33:24,955
I try out something.
You can help me. Look at this.

785
01:33:25,080 --> 01:33:28,868
You push the trigger here.
- And what happens then?

786
01:33:29,000 --> 01:33:33,471
Prush it until I say "now".
And then you turn on the lamp here.

787
01:33:33,600 --> 01:33:36,558
Yes? But remain on the trigger.
- Ok.

788
01:33:40,240 --> 01:33:41,992
Yes.
- Right?

789
01:33:42,320 --> 01:33:44,072
Yes, good!

790
01:33:47,080 --> 01:33:49,640
And now...

791
01:33:51,080 --> 01:33:53,355
Lamp. And out!

792
01:33:55,040 --> 01:33:57,873
Well! It needed to be now.

793
01:34:00,040 --> 01:34:02,873
That interests me.

794
01:34:03,280 --> 01:34:07,796
Picasso played also with light.
Looks really great.

795
01:34:07,920 --> 01:34:10,753
What a nightmare.

796
01:34:11,120 --> 01:34:14,078
What, that picture?
- No, the picture is good.

797
01:34:16,040 --> 01:34:19,999
But it's supposed to actually
please your mother. - Yes.

798
01:34:20,240 --> 01:34:23,789
Now I like it.
- Well, that's fine too.

799
01:34:29,880 --> 01:34:33,839
There, that's it. That's what I mean.
Have you seen it?

800
01:34:35,560 --> 01:34:39,394
Beautiful how he's moving.
Our runner! Or?

801
01:34:40,160 --> 01:34:44,119
He loved snow. He always
freaked out about the first flakes.

802
01:34:44,240 --> 01:34:48,074
Left everything and
and ran outside.

803
01:34:48,200 --> 01:34:52,159
You loved him very much, right?

804
01:34:58,720 --> 01:35:02,679
I didn't always love him.

805
01:35:03,360 --> 01:35:06,909
Everything he did
was so perfect.

806
01:35:07,040 --> 01:35:10,999
I hated that.
I thought Alex is never sad.

807
01:35:11,680 --> 01:35:15,514
He has no reason.
He has no real problem.

808
01:35:17,120 --> 01:35:19,953
I'm such an asshole.

809
01:35:25,640 --> 01:35:28,598
Show me how to dance.

810
01:35:33,920 --> 01:35:36,753
Honestly, I can't.

811
01:35:50,000 --> 01:35:53,390
And now?
- You must guide me, you're the man.

812
01:35:53,520 --> 01:35:56,478
You gotta show what you want.

813
01:36:05,280 --> 01:36:08,113
But it isn't much.

814
01:36:19,680 --> 01:36:20,635
Good!

815
01:36:38,240 --> 01:36:42,074
Say now: I, Max Hollander, am gay.

816
01:36:42,800 --> 01:36:45,360
Real gay.

817
01:36:45,600 --> 01:36:49,479
That seems to fascinate you?

818
01:36:49,600 --> 01:36:52,433
Well, yes. Say it again.

819
01:36:57,360 --> 01:37:01,319
Right now I find it quite difficult.

820
01:37:11,440 --> 01:37:14,000
I must go.

821
01:37:15,120 --> 01:37:17,953
We'll meet soon, ok?

822
01:37:31,560 --> 01:37:34,120
Are you awake?
- No.

823
01:37:34,280 --> 01:37:38,512
I want to visit Alexander's boarding school.
I must find out something. - Good luck.

824
01:37:38,640 --> 01:37:41,473
Are you coming? Please.

825
01:37:41,840 --> 01:37:45,674
No.
- Great. I'll pick you up by 10.

826
01:38:15,080 --> 01:38:17,913
Hello, Johannes.
- Hey.

827
01:38:18,240 --> 01:38:22,279
Sorry, I had to get this stuff.
- Nice that it worked.

828
01:38:22,400 --> 01:38:25,358
This is Max, a friend.
- Hello.

829
01:38:25,480 --> 01:38:30,634
You have test soon, right?
- I'll wait outside.

830
01:38:31,400 --> 01:38:35,439
I'm hungry. Do you want anything?
- Yes, I'd take a coffee.

831
01:38:35,560 --> 01:38:38,472
Alex has told a lot about you.
- Really?

832
01:38:39,560 --> 01:38:40,515
Yep.

833
01:38:41,320 --> 01:38:45,871
Now it's a year ago
but it doesn't get any better.

834
01:38:47,280 --> 01:38:51,114
I can imagine.
- A coffee, please.

835
01:38:53,480 --> 01:38:56,438
You took the picture, right?

836
01:38:59,600 --> 01:39:04,355
Max has painted
a picture of Alex and me.

837
01:39:04,480 --> 01:39:09,315
He used this photo,
because the expression in Alex's face.

838
01:39:09,440 --> 01:39:13,069
He thinks Alex looks
as if he's in love.

839
01:39:13,200 --> 01:39:16,875
I agree somehow,
what do you think?

840
01:39:17,000 --> 01:39:20,879
It's something in the eyes.
My father told me

841
01:39:21,000 --> 01:39:26,233
that you took the picture.
I thought that if Alex was gay

842
01:39:26,880 --> 01:39:31,954
and didn't dare, right?
My parents would freak out.

843
01:39:32,080 --> 01:39:37,473
Perhaps it could be the reason and...
Sorry. It's totally stupid.

844
01:39:37,600 --> 01:39:41,195
You need to go?
- No, I've still a moment.

845
01:39:41,320 --> 01:39:45,871
I'd love to provide a solution.
But Alex and I,

846
01:39:46,000 --> 01:39:49,549
we shared a room, nothing more.

847
01:39:53,320 --> 01:39:57,279
And Alex had nothing with guys
I don't think so.

848
01:39:58,680 --> 01:40:01,638
He was just madly closed.

849
01:40:01,760 --> 01:40:05,719
I mean, he was cheerful.
Always cool sayings and such.

850
01:40:05,840 --> 01:40:09,799
And there was nobody
having anything against him.

851
01:40:10,960 --> 01:40:14,794
But actually nobody knew
much about him.

852
01:40:15,080 --> 01:40:18,959
He was for people exactly
how they wanted him.

853
01:40:19,080 --> 01:40:23,039
Always stay cool, you know?

854
01:40:23,240 --> 01:40:26,198
Maybe he was a bit alone.

855
01:40:30,640 --> 01:40:35,031
Sorry. I mean that I had nothing
going on with your brother.

856
01:40:39,600 --> 01:40:43,434
But I remember very well that night,
when I took the picture.

857
01:40:43,560 --> 01:40:47,439
We hung around, smoked,
drank tequila or something.

858
01:40:47,560 --> 01:40:50,472
It was already 2:00 or so.

859
01:40:50,600 --> 01:40:56,516
I played with my camera,
and we talked about our homes.

860
01:40:56,880 --> 01:41:01,396
I told about my parents,
and he about you.

861
01:41:05,560 --> 01:41:09,519
Exactly, that's the expression
in his face.

862
01:41:11,200 --> 01:41:14,158
He talked about you.

863
01:41:34,480 --> 01:41:37,040
Here you go.
- Thank you.

864
01:41:39,640 --> 01:41:43,599
I've fucked it up...
- Great, just put the gas station on fire.

865
01:41:45,360 --> 01:41:46,315
Yes.

866
01:41:48,360 --> 01:41:53,036
Don't take yourself so important.
Maybe it wasn't even about you.

867
01:41:53,160 --> 01:41:56,709
Then we all screwed
it up together.

868
01:41:57,080 --> 01:42:01,676
You must stop looking for a reason
'cause there's probably more than just one.

869
01:42:05,520 --> 01:42:10,514
And you must stop to be mad at him.
- Mad? I'm not mad!

870
01:42:10,800 --> 01:42:13,758
Yes, because he makes you feel guilty.

871
01:42:14,840 --> 01:42:18,799
I know that, believe me.
I know it pretty well.

872
01:42:22,800 --> 01:42:25,633
Come on, let's continue.

873
01:42:28,000 --> 01:42:30,833
What will happen to me?

874
01:42:32,120 --> 01:42:35,112
What do you want from me?

875
01:42:35,600 --> 01:42:39,149
Who I am, am I me? How strange?

876
01:42:40,240 --> 01:42:43,073
Leave me, go away. Help!

877
01:42:51,920 --> 01:42:55,913
We'll get you, chase you through
the dirt, we'll grab you...

878
01:50:03,680 --> 01:50:08,231
It's me, Lilli.
I've been thinking about the coat.

879
01:50:08,560 --> 01:50:12,109
You wanted to go shopping with me.

880
01:50:16,240 --> 01:50:20,074
Oh, forget that fucking coat, Mom.
Actually...

881
01:50:21,920 --> 01:50:25,879
I just wanted to say
it will good again. Yes?

882
01:50:26,800 --> 01:50:29,360
It will be good again.

883
01:50:31,280 --> 01:50:33,236
Good night.

884
01:50:42,440 --> 01:50:46,399
It's me Lilli.
I've been thinking about the coat.

885
01:50:53,640 --> 01:50:57,189
You know already,
what do you'll do next?

886
01:50:58,200 --> 01:51:01,749
Look to the right. No idea.

887
01:51:04,120 --> 01:51:08,079
I probably need to get out here.
Find faces,

888
01:51:08,480 --> 01:51:12,393
people in the streets...
- Sounds good.

889
01:51:19,600 --> 01:51:23,149
Well, this picture is at least ready now.

890
01:51:29,200 --> 01:51:32,158
I must go. I have an appointment.

891
01:51:34,760 --> 01:51:38,594
Oh wait, again.
I've got a little thing for you.

892
01:51:38,840 --> 01:51:42,389
I want to give it to you. Look here.

893
01:51:43,760 --> 01:51:47,719
Well, it was an attempt.
Isn't all that bad, right?

894
01:51:56,680 --> 01:51:57,635
Thank you.

895
01:52:05,760 --> 01:52:08,320
Let me see.

896
01:52:12,080 --> 01:52:15,914
I'll miss you.
- Yes, yes, I understand.

897
01:52:24,680 --> 01:52:28,355
About a year ago
we've lost Alexander.

898
01:52:28,480 --> 01:52:31,438
He took his own life.

899
01:52:33,320 --> 01:52:36,278
We still don't know why.

900
01:52:41,800 --> 01:52:46,237
And who are they now?
- The children of my customer.

901
01:52:51,360 --> 01:52:53,920
This is Lilli.

902
01:52:54,440 --> 01:52:58,274
She's studying singing and dancing in Munich.
- Singing and dancing.

903
01:52:58,400 --> 01:53:01,233
You can study it?

904
01:53:01,480 --> 01:53:05,871
And the mother wanted a beautiful
paintings of her two beautiful children?

905
01:53:06,320 --> 01:53:08,880
That's right.

906
01:53:10,040 --> 01:53:14,591
I love these rich people.
What would we do without them?

907
01:53:32,600 --> 01:53:35,160
Who is it?

908
01:53:36,000 --> 01:53:38,560
My father.

909
01:53:38,800 --> 01:53:41,758
Hey, Stella, are you coming?

910
01:53:43,920 --> 01:53:47,469
Hi.
- Hello, Tobi. Happy birthday.

911
01:53:49,160 --> 01:53:50,115
Thank you.

912
01:53:51,720 --> 01:53:54,678
How was Spain? Salamanca?

913
01:53:55,640 --> 01:53:56,595
Cool.

914
01:53:57,920 --> 01:54:00,753
I want to give you this.

915
01:54:08,360 --> 01:54:09,315
Thank you.

916
01:54:13,200 --> 01:54:16,158
Is that your girlfriend?
- Yes.

917
01:54:18,680 --> 01:54:21,513
What's her name?
- Stella.

918
01:54:21,680 --> 01:54:24,478
Stella. Pretty.

919
01:54:27,400 --> 01:54:30,358
Yes, well, then. Thank you for the picture.

920
01:54:32,360 --> 01:54:35,318
Well, maybe you have it inside..

921
01:54:36,080 --> 01:54:39,038
Maybe it's snowing tonight.
- Ok.

922
01:54:42,800 --> 01:54:44,756
Ciao, Dad.

923
01:54:46,360 --> 01:54:48,920
Well, take care.

924
01:54:56,960 --> 01:54:59,793
Bye, Mr. Hollander!

925
01:55:00,920 --> 01:55:04,515
Goodbye, Stella.
Could you take care of the picture?

926
01:55:04,640 --> 01:55:08,474
I don't want it gets wet, ok?
- Will do!

927
01:55:24,320 --> 01:55:28,279
What are you doing?
- I couldn't sleep.

928
01:55:29,400 --> 01:55:35,032
So I thought I could as well start.
- It's only in two weeks.

929
01:55:35,480 --> 01:55:38,438
Everything shall be beautiful
when she's coming.

930
01:55:49,640 --> 01:55:53,474
Want one?
- Why not.

931
01:56:09,320 --> 01:56:12,392
Have you already told her?
- What?

932
01:56:14,120 --> 01:56:16,680
That you move out.

933
01:56:17,320 --> 01:56:20,278
No. I'll do it when she's here.

934
01:56:23,680 --> 01:56:27,229
We had also
good times together, right?

935
01:56:28,280 --> 01:56:29,235
Absolutely!

936
01:57:50,160 --> 01:57:53,470
Alex! We stop that nonsense now!

937
01:57:54,600 --> 01:57:56,113
It's enough!

938
01:58:56,160 --> 01:58:59,118
Ok, ok, apologies accepted.

939
01:59:06,160 --> 01:59:10,118
English subtitles:
A Huge Animal From The North